                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 Roszkowski, Mieczyslaw/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-12T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 12, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. Your 1804, December 30, 6 p.m. The Soviet Ambassador informed Mr. Welles on
                    January 15 that in view of apparent American citizenship of Roszkowski, his
                    Government had agreed to reopen the case.</p>
                <p>You may care, therefore, to continue to press Soviet authorities with regard to
                    this matter and to ask that a representative of the Embassy be permitted to
                    visit him in prison. Please keep Department informed of developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
